practitioner.about:
Dr. Fatma Al Madani is a Physician Consultant in Dermatology at Medcare Medical Centre. She completed her basic medical education from Cairo University, Egypt and her internship trainee rotation with the Department of Health, Dubai. She did her post-graduation at Cardiff University (UK) and trained in dermatology at the Heath Hospital.

Dr. Madani has spent more than three decades working under the aegis of the Dubai Health Authority as a Dermatologist and panel member for choosing new Dermatologists. She commenced her sterling career as a trainee and then joined as registrar in the Dermatology department at Dubai Hospital, Rashid Hospital and Maktoum Hospital under DHA. While working in Government Hospitals she was promoted to Senior Registrar and then to Consultant Dermatologist, specialising in Dermatology, Venereology and Cosmetology. Later, she worked as a Specialist and Consultant in Dermatology, at several well-known private hospitals and clinics in the UAE, including the Aesthetica Clinic, the Dubai Medical Group, the Al Tamayoz Medical Centre, the Al Garhoud Private Hospital, the Sehaty Polyclinic and the Hyf Medical Centre.

Dr. Madani’s expertise ranges from Clinical Dermatology and Aesthetic Dermatology to Paediatric Dermatology. She is proficient in various cosmetic procedures, laser treatments, acne and scar management, immuno-dermatology, anti-ageing and skin rejuvenation, skin cancer screening and treatment, dermatosurgery and minor procedures, Botox and fillers, chemical peels, microdermabrasion, PRP therapy for hair and skin and advanced wound care. She has successfully treated pigmentation disorders, skin allergies, hair and scalp disorders, nail disorders, psoriasis and autoimmune skin diseases, eczema, chronic skin conditions, and fungal and bacterial skin infections.

In her spare time, she likes to catch up on her reading. She speaks Arabic and English.
